  "brief": "<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Market Overview</h2>\n\nRisk-on rally building steam pre-market with Russell 2000 leading at +2.16% and Dow showing surprising strength at +1.77%. VIX drop to 28.98 suggests some tension relief despite ongoing Iran headlines dominating the tape.\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> What to Watch</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Treasury Auctions:</strong> 3-month and 6-month bill auctions at 3:30 PM will test demand amid geopolitical uncertainty</li>\n<li><strong>Energy Sector Weakness:</strong> XLE down -2.76% despite Middle East tensions - watch for reversal or continuation</li>\n<li><strong>Iran Ceasefire Developments:</strong> Market pricing in diplomacy hopes while US ship seizure adds complexity</li>\n<li><strong>Small Cap Breakout:</strong> IWM leading charge suggests domestic focus over international concerns</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-amber\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚡ Key Driver</div>Market torn between geopolitical risk and diplomatic optimism - Iran's emphasis on diplomacy providing relief valve for oversold conditions</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Sector Rotation</h2>\n\nClassic risk-on rotation with Consumer Discretionary (+2.36%) and Industrials (+1.87%) leading while defensive Utilities lag at -0.41%. Energy's -2.76% drop paradoxical given Middle East tensions, suggesting traders betting on de-escalation. Tech and Healthcare both strong above +1.4% indicates broad-based appetite returning.\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-green\"><div class=\"callout-label\">✦ Bull Case</div>Small caps outperforming signals domestic confidence returning. VIX decline from elevated levels creates technical tailwind for momentum continuation.</div>\n\n<div class=\"callout callout-red\"><div class=\"callout-label\">⚠ Bear Case</div>Energy sector weakness despite Iran tensions suggests underlying demand concerns. Treasury auctions could reveal funding stress if poorly received.</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"sec-icon\">◆</span> Levels That Matter</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>SPY 712:</strong> Key resistance - break above confirms continuation of relief rally</li>\n<li><strong>QQQ 650:</strong> Psychological level and prior support turned resistance</li>\n<li><strong>VIX 27:</strong> Break below signals meaningful fear reduction</li>\n<li><strong>IWM 280:</strong> Small cap breakout level - failure here kills domestic optimism narrative</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr>\n<p><em>Not a prediction. A preparation. Make your plan before the bell.</em></p>"
